dc_description_s: The E4 PLSS database, part of a multi-year effort, was created as a sub-project of the greater Version 8 Statewide Parcel Map Database Project (V8 Project), a collaboration between the Wisconsin Land Information Program, the State Cartographerâ€™s Office, and county data contributors. More information about the Statewide Parcel Map Initiative can be found here: https://doa.wi.gov/Pages/LocalGovtsGrants/Parcel-Initiative.aspx The E4 database contains a collection of all uniquely identifiable local-level PLSS data available in digital format, and aggregates that data into a standardized schema and format. It also includes section, quarter-section, and quarter-quarter-section level polygons. The construction of the PLSS corner locations contained within the database relies on the local level coordinate information. This unique aspect of the database, allows for an accurate representation of the on-the-ground location of the PLSS corners.Please complete the feedback survey form: https://uwmadison.co1.qualtrics.com/jfe/form/SV_b8ygrYp2ClzG6KW Schema documentation can be found here: https://www.sco.wisc.edu/parcels/data/assets/V8/E4_Wisconsin_PLSS_2022_Database_Documentation.pdf
uw_supplemental_s: This is an archived copy of the data held at UW-Madison. For access to the most recent data please visit: https://www.sco.wisc.edu/parcels/data/
